cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with scaling up coordinate descent algorithms for large L1 regularization problems, which is a common problem in machine learning. It could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it presents a generic framework for parallel coordinate descent algorithms. Additionally, it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it deals with optimization algorithms, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it presents novel parallel algorithms, and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses implementation and performance measurements.
